          "text": "<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Herbal medicine which is not known to be effective</span></span></span></span></p>"
        }
      ],
      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Which of the following is a type of placebo?</span></span></span></span></p>",
      "unique_key": "Q4849966",
      "question_audio": null,
      "question_video": null,
      "map_id": 35859,
      "difficulty_level": "difficult",
      "subjects_id": [
        4
      ],
      "solution": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Ans. A) Sham surgery</span></span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Option A:</span></span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">A <strong>placebo is a substance</strong> or <strong>treatment with no therapeutic effect</strong>, often <strong>used in clinical trials</strong> as a <strong>control to test the efficacy</strong> of a <strong>treatment.</strong> The options provided include different types of interventions, and we need to identify which one can be considered a type of placebo:</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">This is a <strong>type of placebo</strong>. <strong>Sham surgery</strong> is a <strong>procedure that mimics actual surgery </strong>without performing the therapeutic part of the operation. It is <strong>used in clinical trials</strong> to <strong>evaluate the effectiveness</strong> of <strong>surgical procedures</strong> by comparing outcomes with those who underwent the actual surgery.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><strong><u><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Explanation:</span></span></u></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Option B. Physiotherapy:&nbsp;</span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Physiotherapy is a <strong>therapeutic practice</strong> that <strong>involves physical techniques</strong>, such as <strong>exercise, massage,</strong> or <strong>manipulation, to improve body function</strong>. It is a genuine treatment method for various conditions and is not considered a placebo.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Option C. Cognitive Behavioral Therapy (CBT):&nbsp;</span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">CBT is a <strong>type of psychotherapy </strong>that helps <strong>people understand</strong> and <strong>change their thoughts and behaviors.</strong> It is a well-established treatment for various mental health conditions and is not a placebo.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Option D. Herbal medicine which is not known to be effective:&nbsp;</span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">If an <strong>herbal medicine</strong> is <strong>not known to be effective</strong>, it could potentially be <strong>used as a placebo in clinical trials</strong>. However, the key aspect of a placebo is that it is known to be<strong> inert or ineffective for the condition being treated</strong>. Simply being &quot;not known to be effective&quot; does not automatically make an herbal medicine a placebo; it must also be proven to have no therapeutic effect for the specific condition being studied.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><strong><u><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Educational Objective: </span></span></u></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">The correct answer is <strong>Sham surgery,</strong> which is <strong>used as a placebo control in clinical trials</strong> to <strong>determine the effectiveness of surgical procedures</strong> and to <strong>isolate the therapeutic effect</strong> from the <strong>placebo effect.</strong></span></span></span></span></p>",
